meaningMnemonic: <kanji>Membrane</kanji>s that wrap around at an <kanji>angle</kanji> are in your eye. Eyes are round and the membranes have to bend around the front part at an angle. It's called your <vocabulary>cornea</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You should be able to read this on your own.
